atischer Perspektive. Erst dadurch wird sein Verständnis des Dämonischen vor dem Hintergrund der vielschichtigen Kontroversen um diese Deutungskategorie des Ambivalenten in den philosophischen und theologischen Debatten des 20. Jahrhunderts prägnant herausgearbeitet.  aThe notion of the demonic is a key category in the philosophical–theological works of Paul Tillich. This volume discusses this fundamental idea in religious philosophy, theology, and cultural theory in terms of its problematic history and its systematic function in Tillich’s theory of religion.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aGood and evil. 4aDämonisches. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aPhilosophie. 4aTheologie. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / History.2bisacsh  aDemon.  acultural studies.  aphilosophy.  atheology.1 aDanz, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDanz, Christian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDumas, Marc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller, Lutz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOpel, Angela M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRohls, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaal, Christina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchwab, Philipp, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchüz, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchüßler, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchüßler, Werner, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aVoigt, Friedemann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWesterink, Herman, 